[{"location":"#DataIO-1","page":"Home","title":"DataIO","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for DataIO, the Julia port of the DataIO R package. This package provides functions for reading and writing of data files consisting of [n,k] matrices.","category":"page"},{"location":"lrn/#LRN-1","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"LRN","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lrn/#File-structure-1","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"File structure","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lrn/#","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"Data (*.lrn)","text":"The *.lrn file contains the input data as tab separated values. Features in columns, datasets in rows. The first column should be a unique integer key. The optional header contains descriptions of the columns.","category":"page"},{"location":"lrn/#","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"Data (*.lrn)","text":"# comment\n#\n% n\n% m\n% s1          s2          ..      sm\n% var_name1   var_name2   ..      var_namem\nx11           x12         ..      x1m\nx21           x22         ..      x2m\n.             .           .       .\n.             .           .       .\nxn1           xn2         ..      xnm","category":"page"},{"location":"lrn/#","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"Data (*.lrn)","text":"Element Description\nn Number of datasets\nm Number of columns (including index)\ns_i Type of column: 9 for unique key, 1 for data, 0 to ignore column\nvar_name_i Name for the i-th feature\nx_ij Elements of the data matrix. Decimal numbers denoted by '.', not by ','","category":"page"},{"location":"lrn/#Code-Documentation-1","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"Code Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"lrn/#","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"Data (*.lrn)","text":"Modules = [DataIO.LRN]","category":"page"},{"location":"lrn/#DataIO.LRN.LRNCType","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"DataIO.LRN.LRNCType","text":"LRNCType\n\nEnum representing the column types for LRNData:\n\nignore = 0, data = 1, class = 3\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"lrn/#DataIO.LRN.LRNData","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"DataIO.LRN.LRNData","text":"LRNData\n\nLRNData represents the contents of a *.lrn file with the following fields:\n\ndata::Matrix{Float64}\nMatrix of data, cases in rows, variables in columns\ncolumn_types::Array{LRNCType, 1}\nColumn types, see LRNCType\nkeys::Array{Integer, 1}\nUnique key for each line\nnames::Array{String, 1}\nColumn names\nkey_name::String\nName for key column\ncomment::String\nComments about the data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"lrn/#DataIO.LRN.LRNData-Tuple{Array{Float64,2}}","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"DataIO.LRN.LRNData","text":"LRNData(data;\n        column_types=[9,1,1...],\n        keys=[1,2,3...],\n        names=[\"C1\",\"C2\",\"C3\"...],\n        key_name=\"Key\",\n        comment=\"\"\n)\n\nConvenience constructor for LRNData. Uses sensible defaults.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"lrn/#DataIO.LRN.readLRN","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"DataIO.LRN.readLRN","text":"readLRN(filename::String, directory=pwd())\n\nRead the contents of a *.lrn and return a LRNData struct.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"lrn/#DataIO.LRN.writeLRN","page":"Data (*.lrn)","title":"DataIO.LRN.writeLRN","text":"writeLRN(filename::String, lrn::LRNData, directory=pwd())\n\nWrite the contents of a LRNData struct into a file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
